CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 9, 1962, pg. 6 reads: "Westinghouse Honor Grads - According to the faculty of Westinghouse High School, and the National Junior Honor Society, these 36 seniors achieved honor roll status, respectively, during the fast closing 1961-1962 term. Left to right, front row: Robert Lewis, Elmer Burger, Troleta Stewart, Jo Ann Watson, Roger Johnson, Wayne Phinisee, Betty Anderson, Beverly Langford, Lyn Edmunds, Charles Hamilton, James Winston.  Second row: James Hairston, Eric Strasser, Lydia Wynn, Christene Washington, Charlene Davis, Jessica Littleton, Beverly Wright, Frizell Randolph, Robbie Ransaw, Sandra Casey, Jeffrey Alexander, Albert Grice.  Third row: Gene White, Thomas McCracken, Barbara Green, Sanders McGruder, Judith Bradley, Stephanie Mills, Sandra Beasley, Nancy Bailey, Joseph Rhodes, William Butler.  Fourth row: Clifford Britton, Beverly Sinclair, Roderick Hamilton. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Westinghouse High School honor graduates posed on stage with group of musicians seated in foreground
